1
00:00:51,980 --> 00:00:52,980
Mom!

2
00:01:04,790 --> 00:01:06,620
Moon Se Guk lied,

3
00:01:08,690 --> 00:01:09,790
but as for me,

4
00:01:11,260 --> 00:01:12,860
I can cure Min Seo's illness.

5
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:15,060
Every single one of them...

6
00:01:16,630 --> 00:01:17,970
was treated by me.

7
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:24,010
You must be hungry.
Come on, let's go inside.

8
00:01:24,070 --> 00:01:25,940
Mom, can we make a quick stop
at the convenience store first?

9
00:01:26,240 --> 00:01:27,510
There's something I'm really craving.

10
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:30,380
Gosh. Fine. Let's go.

11
00:01:31,180 --> 00:01:33,920
Excuse me?

12
00:01:35,350 --> 00:01:37,690
Are you Kang Sang Woo?

13
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:41,120
Yes, that's me.

14
00:01:42,190 --> 00:01:43,190
You are?

15
00:01:50,330 --> 00:01:51,430
Who are you?

16
00:01:54,140 --> 00:01:55,940
It's just that...

17
00:02:01,180 --> 00:02:05,550
(The Savior’s Quagmire)

18
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:26,740
(Case: Serial murders,
Guam City serial murder and desecration)

19
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:30,170
(Prosecution)

20
00:02:42,450 --> 00:02:44,520
This is Cha Yi Yeon
from Violent Crimes Unit One.

21
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:49,590
I'll cut to the chase.
We've found all the victims' bodies.

22
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:56,030
But to be blunt, we didn't find them.
Lee Woo Gyeom confessed.

23
00:02:56,570 --> 00:02:58,770
Where did you dump the remaining victims?

24
00:02:59,140 --> 00:03:00,700
On the mid-slope of Mount Cheonggye,

25
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:03,040
facing the river,
at the 100-meter mark.

26
00:03:03,540 --> 00:03:04,910
Is he trying to get a reduced sentence?

27
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:08,080
Yes. He asked me about a plea bargain.

28
00:03:08,410 --> 00:03:10,310
I don't want a lighter sentence.

29
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:12,150
I want to make a different kind of deal.

30
00:03:12,950 --> 00:03:17,450
To this day, the number of victims,
their identities, the body locations...

31
00:03:17,820 --> 00:03:20,190
He's never given a straight answer
about any of it.

32
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:23,260
He's toying with us even as we speak.

33
00:03:24,090 --> 00:03:25,830
He has no regard for human life,

34
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:28,400
He's deceiving the entire nation watching,

35
00:03:29,370 --> 00:03:31,430
all while looking down on us from above.

36
00:03:32,140 --> 00:03:34,870
So what's your point?

37
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:38,740
Now it's your turn to cross the line,
Prosecutor Cha.

38
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:41,140
Come over to my side.

39
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:43,480
I will personally show you in court.

40
00:03:43,910 --> 00:03:47,180
How I can save a life
without so much as a scalpel.

41
00:03:48,580 --> 00:03:50,620
You crazy punk...

42
00:03:53,620 --> 00:03:56,030
We will be seeking the death penalty.

43
00:03:59,130 --> 00:04:01,360
(The Establishment of Law and Order)

44
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:06,840
You seem more at ease today.

45
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:10,270
I just came from seeing Sang Woo.

46
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:12,340
That's just like you, Attorney Park.

47
00:04:13,610 --> 00:04:14,680
What do you mean? "Just like me?"

48
00:04:16,350 --> 00:04:17,680
You think you know me?

49
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:22,550
That you're a good father
who loves Min Seo more than anything...

50
00:04:22,620 --> 00:04:25,820
Don't talk so casually about my daughter.

51
00:04:26,490 --> 00:04:28,520
Gosh, it was a compliment.
That's a little harsh.

52
00:04:29,390 --> 00:04:32,130
Did you really cure Sang Woo?

53
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:33,930
Didn't you see him walking?

54
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,700
That Sang Woo was cured because of you.
That's something I...

55
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,040
How am I supposed to believe that?

56
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:43,940
Good.

57
00:04:45,210 --> 00:04:46,810
You should keep doubting me.

58
00:04:47,510 --> 00:04:49,780
That's the only way
you'll want to see the real thing.

59
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:53,320
Attorney Park,

60
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:57,950
when people come back from the dead,

61
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,920
they come to realize
more than what meets the eye.

62
00:05:02,130 --> 00:05:04,790
I was in a coma for three years
after a car accident.

63
00:05:12,940 --> 00:05:14,600
I had no idea how I woke up,

64
00:05:15,170 --> 00:05:17,670
much less why.

65
00:05:19,210 --> 00:05:23,080
My doctor said I had a new blood mutation,

66
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:27,350
but I couldn't just take his word for it.

67
00:05:28,350 --> 00:05:30,920
I was just an ordinary med student
back then.

68
00:05:34,190 --> 00:05:36,060
But there was another problem.

69
00:05:38,460 --> 00:05:39,860
As an aftereffect of the accident,

70
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:43,470
waves of pain would hit me out of nowhere.

71
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:50,870
The exact same pain
I felt during the car crash.

72
00:05:57,150 --> 00:05:58,780
I couldn't find the cause.

73
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,650
So, since I was living
on borrowed time anyway,

74
00:06:03,590 --> 00:06:05,350
I started experimenting on my own body.

75
00:06:07,690 --> 00:06:10,260
I did all sorts of crazy things,
not caring if I died.

76
00:06:12,090 --> 00:06:14,530
I injected myself with anything
that could possibly be a cure.

77
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:21,400
But then one day,

78
00:06:22,510 --> 00:06:23,970
the pain was gone.

79
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:27,540
I had created a cure
for an incurable disease.

80
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:30,410
For the very disease that
they said was untreatable.

81
00:06:31,550 --> 00:06:35,280
The pain, the aftereffects of the coma...
They were all gone.

82
00:06:37,790 --> 00:06:40,960
You're saying you found a cure?

83
00:06:41,890 --> 00:06:45,800
Yes. And I realized that method
could be used to cure other diseases too.

84
00:06:48,660 --> 00:06:49,770
You can really...

85
00:06:50,830 --> 00:06:52,300
You can cure the Batten disease,
can't you?

86
00:07:01,380 --> 00:07:03,180
No one believed me at first.

87
00:07:06,450 --> 00:07:08,080
But they all survived,

88
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:11,250
and every single person who woke up
was grateful to me.

89
00:07:14,220 --> 00:07:15,490
Life and death...

90
00:07:16,860 --> 00:07:18,260
It's nothing to me.

91
00:07:23,670 --> 00:07:25,230
(Court)

92
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:28,440
- Bring back the death penalty!
- Bring it back!

93
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:31,410
- Bring it back!
- Harsh punishment for violent criminals!

94
00:07:31,470 --> 00:07:33,610
- Punish them!
- Punish them!

95
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:35,950
- That's Lee Woo Gyeom!
- Murderer! Killer!

96
00:07:36,050 --> 00:07:37,550
- Killer!
- Murderer!

97
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:43,090
- Lee Woo Gyeom, you murderer!
- Hey, killer!

98
00:07:44,090 --> 00:07:47,060
- Bring back the death penalty!
- Bring it back!

99
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,390
Following the arrest of
serial killer Lee Woo Gyeom,

100
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:53,460
public support for resuming executions
has been rising dramatically.

101
00:07:53,860 --> 00:07:55,100
According to a recent poll,

102
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:57,630
a staggering 74.3 percent
of respondents said...

103
00:07:57,730 --> 00:08:01,070
they were in favor of resuming executions.

104
00:08:01,370 --> 00:08:03,670
Meanwhile, the attorney
handling Lee Woo Gyeom's trial,

105
00:08:03,740 --> 00:08:07,140
Park Han Jun,
is also facing continued controversy.

106
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:09,550
Attorney Park was
formerly a prosecutor for...

107
00:08:09,550 --> 00:08:10,850
the Central Investigation Department...

108
00:08:10,910 --> 00:08:13,580
before becoming a civil rights attorney.
However, in recent years...

109
00:08:23,590 --> 00:08:27,200
The defendant killed 17 people.
Is that correct?

110
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,600
Yes.

111
00:08:28,860 --> 00:08:32,000
And you claim you killed them
while experimenting to create a cure?

112
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:35,200
- Yes, that's correct.
- Assuming your claim is true,

113
00:08:35,740 --> 00:08:37,970
the process
in which 17 people were killed.

114
00:08:38,370 --> 00:08:42,110
- Where are the records of that research?
- Your Honor.

115
00:08:42,780 --> 00:08:48,220
The records in Exhibit 23 contain
the research on the 17 victims.

116
00:08:48,450 --> 00:08:49,490
Your Honor.

117
00:08:49,990 --> 00:08:53,890
However, the victims' bodies
are so severely mutilated...

118
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:57,990
that the National Forensic Service reports
they can't confirm their identities.

119
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:00,130
(Prosecution)

120
00:09:10,070 --> 00:09:11,070
Defendant!

121
00:09:11,940 --> 00:09:16,550
If your goal was research,
why dismember the victims so brutally?

122
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:18,910
If your goal was truly research, then why!

123
00:09:19,820 --> 00:09:23,890
Why did Hong Jae Gwang have to be murdered
and left in such a wretched state?

124
00:09:28,660 --> 00:09:30,690
(Defendant)

125
00:09:33,330 --> 00:09:34,330
Your Honor.

126
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,630
If the defendant's true intention
was research,

127
00:09:38,730 --> 00:09:43,210
would he have needed to desecrate
the victims' bodies to such an extent?

128
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:45,040
How interesting.

129
00:09:45,510 --> 00:09:47,280
Therefore, we contend that this case...

130
00:09:47,940 --> 00:09:50,710
is just a series of thrill kills
by a psychopathic murderer.

131
00:09:50,780 --> 00:09:51,780
Your Honor.

132
00:09:53,050 --> 00:09:55,180
The prosecution's assertion
of "thrill kills" is...

133
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:58,550
merely an emotional argument
with no evidence whatsoever.

134
00:09:58,990 --> 00:10:02,390
Sustained.
Prosecutor, do you have any grounds?

135
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:05,090
Yes. I'll present them now.

136
00:10:07,130 --> 00:10:08,130
Defendant.

137
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:11,530
You're familiar with
Jo Gyeong Chan, correct?

138
00:10:11,870 --> 00:10:12,870
Yes.

139
00:10:12,940 --> 00:10:16,740
Five years ago, you were hit by a car
driven by Jo Gyeong Chan,

140
00:10:17,170 --> 00:10:21,880
which left you in a coma for three years.
How did you feel about that?

141
00:10:22,450 --> 00:10:23,550
You must have been angry, right?

142
00:10:24,380 --> 00:10:27,980
Resentful that this happened to you.
And over time,

143
00:10:28,850 --> 00:10:30,850
towards the person responsible
for the accident,

144
00:10:31,890 --> 00:10:33,890
you must have felt anger
and a desire for revenge.

145
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,390
- That's not true.
- It's not?

146
00:10:36,460 --> 00:10:37,460
No, it is not.

147
00:10:37,530 --> 00:10:40,000
Then why did you seek out
and murder Jo Gyeong Chan?

148
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:41,330
Jo Gyeong Chan?

149
00:11:11,830 --> 00:11:14,530
Your Honor. The defendant's crimes...

150
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:18,600
were premeditated murders born
from anger and a desire for revenge.

151
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:22,740
He targeted adults whose disappearances
were unlikely to be investigated,

152
00:11:22,810 --> 00:11:26,640
making this a clear case
of calculated serial murder.

153
00:11:27,180 --> 00:11:29,780
I submit their traffic accident record
as evidence.

154
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:32,410
The accident between the defendant
and the victim, Jo Gyeong Chan,

155
00:11:48,130 --> 00:11:51,030
- Look at him.
- Darn... He's a monster.

156
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:53,170
Stop provoking them.

157
00:11:53,470 --> 00:11:55,570
I'm not provoking them. It's just absurd.

158
00:11:56,810 --> 00:11:58,910
- Look at him. My goodness.
- Order!

159
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:00,910
I will have you removed
from the courtroom if not.

160
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:04,210
(Defendant)

161
00:12:06,850 --> 00:12:08,950
Counsel for the defense, your rebuttal.

162
00:12:09,850 --> 00:12:12,560
(Defense Counsel)

163
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:14,190
Your Honor.

164
00:12:16,330 --> 00:12:17,690
The prosecution's argument...

165
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,560
does have some merit.

166
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:25,070
And that's because you have yet to hear
the details of how my client...

167
00:12:25,470 --> 00:12:27,400
performed his treatments.

168
00:12:29,810 --> 00:12:33,210
Are you saying you can explain
the treatment process?

169
00:12:33,940 --> 00:12:35,040
I won't just explain it.

170
00:12:36,710 --> 00:12:39,920
I'll show you firsthand.

171
00:12:43,190 --> 00:12:47,520
I would like to call as witnesses
the six terminally ill patients...

172
00:12:49,260 --> 00:12:50,560
whom the defendant claims to have cured.

173
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:01,840
So who are the witnesses?

174
00:13:04,470 --> 00:13:05,570
I still have to find them.

175
00:13:06,010 --> 00:13:07,010
What?

176
00:13:07,510 --> 00:13:09,080
So you were just bluffing?

177
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:11,310
I had to shift the momentum of the trial.

178
00:13:11,650 --> 00:13:14,120
It was leaning in Prosecutor Cha's favor
from the start.

179
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:19,790
You make it sound like it's my fault.

180
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,390
That's because it is.

181
00:13:22,290 --> 00:13:25,290
Why did you have to mutilate
the bodies like that?

182
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:28,500
You only call it "mutilation"
because you see it as murder.

183
00:13:29,470 --> 00:13:31,600
"Why are you dissecting a frog
so cruelly?"

184
00:13:31,930 --> 00:13:33,470
That's the exact same question.

185
00:13:33,870 --> 00:13:34,940
But Hong Jae Gwang was different.

186
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:37,370
Because the experiment with him
was a success.

187
00:13:38,710 --> 00:13:41,680
So you drained all of his blood?

188
00:13:41,780 --> 00:13:45,350
Yes, that's when I figured out
how to create the cure.

189
00:13:50,650 --> 00:13:52,050
To you, when it comes to your experiments,

190
00:13:53,220 --> 00:13:54,890
murder is just part of the process.

191
00:13:58,460 --> 00:14:02,130
If Hong Jae Gwang's experiment failed,
you wouldn't have stopped at 17, right?

192
00:14:02,830 --> 00:14:04,230
Just be honest with me.

193
00:14:05,370 --> 00:14:06,470
Stop lying.

194
00:14:06,940 --> 00:14:09,670
- Lie about what?
- Because you wanted to kill him.

195
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:11,940
That's why you killed him.

196
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:16,080
That's why you killed
Jo Gyeong Chan first, isn't it?

197
00:14:17,450 --> 00:14:19,750
Be honest with me about your motive,

198
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:24,890
and let's focus on proving your ability.
If you're caught lying in court,

199
00:14:25,820 --> 00:14:26,920
you won't escape the death penalty.

200
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,490
I don't care.

201
00:14:29,090 --> 00:14:31,090
They won't execute me anyway.

202
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:36,900
Besides, would they really execute someone
who can cure the terminally ill?

203
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:41,040
That's only...

204
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,910
if your treatment is recognized.
Only if it's recognized.

205
00:14:47,540 --> 00:14:48,610
That's why...

206
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:52,550
I need you to get my ability recognized
through this trial.

207
00:14:52,650 --> 00:14:54,450
Get those witnesses to testify too.

208
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:57,850
That's the only way to treat Min Seo,
right?

209
00:15:01,290 --> 00:15:03,930
(Hae Gang Law Firm)

210
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:14,500
(Attorney Park Han Jun)

211
00:15:18,870 --> 00:15:19,910
Park Han Jun.

212
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:22,440
Do you really have to
take the Lee Woo Gyeom case?

213
00:15:23,180 --> 00:15:25,850
It's not too late. Please, just drop it.

214
00:15:26,520 --> 00:15:28,420
I'll try to persuade the director again.

215
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:29,720
It's fine.

216
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:35,620
How is this fine?
You're not thinking straight.

217
00:15:36,020 --> 00:15:38,590
Why on earth would you agree
to defend a serial killer?

218
00:15:38,990 --> 00:15:40,530
If you become the public's punching bag,

219
00:15:40,830 --> 00:15:43,570
- what kind of client would hire you?
- I have to do this.

220
00:15:43,770 --> 00:15:44,770
But why?

221
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,900
Why does it have to be you?

222
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:50,210
It's a case I have to take.

223
00:15:51,710 --> 00:15:54,110
For Lee Woo Gyeom... And...

224
00:15:57,580 --> 00:15:58,680
for me.

225
00:16:10,630 --> 00:16:12,490
You are off the route.

226
00:16:22,370 --> 00:16:25,770
Reporter Jo, it's me.
My GPS can't seem to find the place.

227
00:16:26,580 --> 00:16:30,480
The roads around here are a real maze,
so it's hard to find.

228
00:16:30,850 --> 00:16:31,880
What do you see around you?

229
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:34,580
Not much besides the sky,

230
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:37,650
And a long flight of stairs to my right.

231
00:16:37,850 --> 00:16:41,690
- See the sky? Then you're almost here.
- Really?

232
00:16:43,660 --> 00:16:44,660
I see your car.

233
00:16:45,630 --> 00:16:48,930
- I see you.
- Yes. Just keep coming straight up.

234
00:16:50,230 --> 00:16:51,230
Right here.

235
00:16:55,770 --> 00:16:57,540
All right, you're parked, right?

236
00:16:58,810 --> 00:17:00,480
You're here, Attorney Park.

237
00:17:06,550 --> 00:17:08,650
Man, you must've had a hard time
getting here.

238
00:17:13,090 --> 00:17:16,590
Ta-da! Cozy, right?

239
00:17:18,190 --> 00:17:19,190
Goodness.

240
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,000
Gosh.

241
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:26,700
It feels lived in.

242
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,100
Here, let me take that.

243
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:32,010
This is your spot right here.

244
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:34,540
You must be thirsty.
Instant coffee or cold water?

245
00:17:35,010 --> 00:17:36,140
No, I'm good.

246
00:17:36,580 --> 00:17:37,650
Come on, at least let me...

247
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:01,170
Here, have a nice, cold glass.

248
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,240
Don't worry, the water's clean.

249
00:18:10,010 --> 00:18:14,080
If six witnesses claim Lee Woo Gyeom
cured their incurable diseases,

250
00:18:14,150 --> 00:18:16,020
do you think the court will see
the case a little differently?

251
00:18:16,650 --> 00:18:18,090
They'd have to.

252
00:18:18,490 --> 00:18:20,560
It would completely change
the motive for the murders.

253
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,190
Yes.

254
00:18:24,990 --> 00:18:26,230
Right.

255
00:18:27,530 --> 00:18:29,130
About Lee Woo Gyeom,

256
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,130
I heard they're moving him
to solitary confinement.

257
00:18:32,370 --> 00:18:35,140
It's just a psychological tactic
to corner him.

258
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:38,440
This puts us at a disadvantage
in so many ways.

259
00:18:42,540 --> 00:18:43,580
Reporter Jo.

260
00:18:44,310 --> 00:18:45,350
Yes?

261
00:18:47,950 --> 00:18:49,520
How about you write an article for me?

262
00:18:53,490 --> 00:18:55,990
(Why Prosecution Ignores the Truth?)

263
00:18:56,830 --> 00:18:58,260
It's a reporter named Jo Woo Cheol.

264
00:18:58,590 --> 00:19:01,030
He's the one who's clashed with
the financial crimes unit before.

265
00:19:01,830 --> 00:19:03,800
Can't you shut him up?

266
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,070
We don't need to respond
to this kind of tabloid trash.

267
00:19:07,140 --> 00:19:09,170
I'm telling you.
He's working with Attorney Park.

268
00:19:10,070 --> 00:19:11,440
With Attorney Park Han Jun?

269
00:19:11,770 --> 00:19:13,810
This is exactly why I can't relax.

270
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:16,910
I told you to pay attention
to every little detail.

271
00:19:17,950 --> 00:19:19,250
If we make one wrong move...

272
00:19:21,580 --> 00:19:24,150
See? It just becomes a huge pain,
understand?

273
00:19:27,020 --> 00:19:28,260
Yes, hello?

274
00:19:29,390 --> 00:19:30,630
This is Cha Yi Yeon speaking.

275
00:19:31,430 --> 00:19:34,560
Director Oh is unavailable at the moment,
so I'm taking his calls.

276
00:19:37,470 --> 00:19:39,300
Yes, he's doing well,
thank you for asking.

277
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:40,970
By any chance,

278
00:19:41,370 --> 00:19:44,040
are you calling about that strange article
that was published today?

279
00:19:45,140 --> 00:19:49,780
Please don't worry, Chief Prosecutor.
I will take care of this precisely,

280
00:19:49,850 --> 00:19:51,850
and I'll handle it with no loose ends.

281
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:56,650
Yes, of course. The director is back.
One moment, please.

282
00:19:57,020 --> 00:19:58,020
Here you go.

283
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:00,960
"Precisely?"

284
00:20:01,890 --> 00:20:02,960
Don't worry.

285
00:20:03,860 --> 00:20:05,830
Hello, Chief Prosecutor?
This is Director Oh.

286
00:20:06,860 --> 00:20:07,860
Yes.

287
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:09,560
Yes.

288
00:20:14,370 --> 00:20:15,640
Number 5896, in your cell.

289
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:31,890
That's him, right? The serial killer.

290
00:20:32,190 --> 00:20:33,660
Look at that pretty face.

291
00:20:34,190 --> 00:20:38,290
- He's got killer looks.
- Hey, new guy. Don't stare like that.

292
00:20:38,360 --> 00:20:41,530
Lose the death stare.
Hey, what are you lookin' at?

293
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:46,070
Hey, look at this bastard's face.
You killed 17 people, huh?

294
00:20:46,130 --> 00:20:47,670
You disrespectful punk.

295
00:20:47,940 --> 00:20:50,170
Get over here.
I want a good look at your face.

296
00:20:50,970 --> 00:20:53,280
Hey. Hey!

297
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:15,200
(Jaeil Hospital)

298
00:21:15,260 --> 00:21:17,330
(Pediatric Ward Nurses' Station)

299
00:21:20,970 --> 00:21:21,970
Min Seo.

300
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:25,240
Doctor, her breathing is unstable.
Her BP and pulse keep dropping too.

301
00:21:25,470 --> 00:21:28,110
Min Seo, look at Mommy. Min Seo!

302
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:38,520
Hey. What's wrong with Min Seo?

303
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:41,620
It must have been the increased dosage.

304
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:45,360
She's stable for now,
but I'll run some more detailed tests.

305
00:21:52,030 --> 00:21:53,070
Jae Hee.

306
00:21:54,370 --> 00:21:55,370
Let's...

307
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:57,740
Let's try to get that new drug again.

308
00:21:58,470 --> 00:22:00,510
That drug was only tested on adults.

309
00:22:00,780 --> 00:22:03,210
It could be dangerous
for children like Min Seo.

310
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:05,550
But still,

311
00:22:06,050 --> 00:22:08,020
we can't just go through
the same thing day after day.

312
00:22:08,750 --> 00:22:12,290
Doing the same thing over and over
is what's keeping our Min Seo alive.

313
00:22:14,420 --> 00:22:15,460
Listen to me.

314
00:22:16,290 --> 00:22:18,930
I think about our Min Seo all the time.

315
00:22:30,570 --> 00:22:32,770
They said no other patient has held on
as long as our Min Seo has.

316
00:22:34,140 --> 00:22:35,980
We've done so well up to now,

317
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:39,080
so our Min Seo will be fine.

318
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:41,120
You're right.

319
00:22:41,820 --> 00:22:42,950
Our Min Seo...

320
00:22:43,620 --> 00:22:45,050
will get healthy again.

321
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:48,560
And I will make sure she does.

322
00:22:52,730 --> 00:22:53,900
I'm sorry.

323
00:22:55,030 --> 00:22:56,630
Appearing in court...

324
00:22:57,770 --> 00:22:58,930
It's too much for me.

325
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:01,370
Ma'am,

326
00:23:02,370 --> 00:23:03,570
we just need you to testify...

327
00:23:04,610 --> 00:23:06,240
that Sang Woo was treated...

328
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:09,440
by Lee Woo Gyeom. That's all.

329
00:23:09,980 --> 00:23:11,080
My Sang Woo...

330
00:23:12,310 --> 00:23:13,550
Even though he's recovered,

331
00:23:14,250 --> 00:23:16,590
it's still not easy for him
to face the world.

332
00:23:16,850 --> 00:23:18,390
I don't want the whole world to know...

333
00:23:19,250 --> 00:23:20,860
the fact that my son was sick.

334
00:23:23,590 --> 00:23:27,600
If people find out he was treated
by a murderer, what will they think?

335
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,060
I'm sorry.

336
00:23:29,970 --> 00:23:32,600
Wait... Ma'am!

337
00:23:40,410 --> 00:23:41,540
What about the patient, Oh Min Gyu?

338
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:43,750
Have you reached him?

339
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:47,980
His testimony is on record,
but we haven't confirmed his identity yet.

340
00:23:48,150 --> 00:23:52,850
Also, all six patients treated
by Lee Woo Gyeom are refusing to testify.

341
00:23:53,420 --> 00:23:57,030
If we want to bring them in,
we might have to subpoena them.

342
00:23:57,090 --> 00:23:59,930
No, absolutely not. If we do that,

343
00:24:00,830 --> 00:24:03,300
we might not get the testimony we need.

344
00:24:05,130 --> 00:24:07,540
- So, what do we do?
- We just have to keep...

345
00:24:07,970 --> 00:24:09,440
trying to persuade them.

346
00:24:15,410 --> 00:24:18,450
(Oh Min Gyu, 25 years old,
Recovered Batten disease)

347
00:24:18,510 --> 00:24:21,820
(True Rehabilitation)

348
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:24,950
(Strive to Live Righteously)

349
00:24:36,030 --> 00:24:37,730
Something about that punk
just rubs me the wrong way.

350
00:24:38,970 --> 00:24:41,300
I heard that he killed
17 people all by himself.

351
00:24:41,740 --> 00:24:42,800
Seventeen people?

352
00:24:44,040 --> 00:24:46,470
- What crew is he with?
- He's not with any crew.

353
00:24:46,740 --> 00:24:48,110
They say he came up as a lone wolf.

354
00:24:48,810 --> 00:24:49,810
A lone wolf.

355
00:24:52,780 --> 00:24:53,820
Go on.

356
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:55,420
Stare all you want.

357
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:58,150
Once we're in the same cell,
I'll beat you senseless.

358
00:24:59,890 --> 00:25:01,920
- Damn it.
- You fool!

359
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:12,530
(Please be quiet.)

360
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:19,710
Changing the witnesses' minds...

361
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:21,780
is going to take some time.

362
00:25:23,010 --> 00:25:24,050
How cheap.

363
00:25:24,450 --> 00:25:25,950
And to think they were begging me
to save them.

364
00:25:27,350 --> 00:25:29,320
Of all the patients you treated,

365
00:25:29,950 --> 00:25:30,990
by any chance,

366
00:25:31,650 --> 00:25:33,360
do you remember a patient
named Oh Min Gyu?

367
00:25:34,420 --> 00:25:36,620
Yes. The one with Batten disease.

368
00:25:37,290 --> 00:25:38,630
Can you get in touch with him?

369
00:25:38,990 --> 00:25:42,630
No.
Once their treatment is over, that's it.

370
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:45,070
I see.

371
00:25:47,170 --> 00:25:48,570
But it must be nice to be Min Seo.

372
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:51,340
Having a father who only cares about her.

373
00:25:51,710 --> 00:25:52,970
Focus on your case.

374
00:25:55,910 --> 00:25:56,910
Alright, then.

375
00:25:58,380 --> 00:26:01,880
Don't you have some kind of record
of how you treated them?

376
00:26:02,580 --> 00:26:04,550
- Of course I do.
- You do?

377
00:26:06,290 --> 00:26:09,920
But the witnesses have to testify
for the court to admit them as evidence.

378
00:26:10,830 --> 00:26:14,830
Since the witnesses can't testify now,
just submitting those records...

379
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:16,800
is our best shot.

380
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:23,270
If you go to my study,
there should be a red notebook.

381
00:26:23,570 --> 00:26:25,010
That's my research log.

382
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:28,140
But I'm pretty sure
the police have already taken it.

383
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:29,440
They did?

384
00:27:39,950 --> 00:27:41,850
"Human Clinical Trial Results."

385
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:43,220
(Oh Min Gyu, Male, Batten Disease)

386
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:44,290
Batten Disease.

387
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:46,890
(Oh Min Gyu, 25 years old,
Recovered Batten disease)

388
00:28:01,300 --> 00:28:02,300
Hey!

389
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:04,240
Stop right there.

390
00:28:06,510 --> 00:28:07,640
I said stop!

391
00:28:41,810 --> 00:28:44,910
I'm sorry. I won't do it again.
Please, just let me go.

392
00:28:46,780 --> 00:28:49,350
Hey everyone, this is legit the place
where Lee Woo Gyeom...

393
00:28:49,420 --> 00:28:52,450
dismembered his victim. Check this out.

394
00:28:53,760 --> 00:28:55,190
- Hey.
- The vibe in here is insane, right?

395
00:28:55,260 --> 00:28:57,790
Is this that "dare challenge"
that's going around?

396
00:28:58,130 --> 00:29:00,630
Yes. If this video blows up,
I can get ad revenue.

397
00:29:00,630 --> 00:29:04,130
- And the top guys make over a grand.
- Okay, I get it. Hey, Attorney Park.

398
00:29:04,830 --> 00:29:08,740
As you know,
we can't guard the scene 24 hours a day.

399
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:09,840
And besides,

400
00:29:10,370 --> 00:29:13,240
this is on the kid who crossed the tape,
right?

401
00:29:13,310 --> 00:29:14,480
Yes, I'm sorry.

402
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:16,640
You.

403
00:29:18,310 --> 00:29:19,550
Listen to me carefully.

404
00:29:20,150 --> 00:29:23,080
If you lie, you could be charged
with trespassing and obstructing justice,

405
00:29:23,250 --> 00:29:24,520
which means up to three years in prison...

406
00:29:24,790 --> 00:29:26,690
and a fine of up to five grand.
Understand?

407
00:29:29,790 --> 00:29:30,930
Tell me the truth.

408
00:29:31,790 --> 00:29:32,890
Did you go inside...

409
00:29:34,100 --> 00:29:35,460
or not?

410
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:38,630
I swear I only filmed nearby.

411
00:29:38,700 --> 00:29:40,370
Besides, the doors were all locked.

412
00:29:40,700 --> 00:29:42,800
So you tried the doors, didn't you?

413
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:44,770
You can't lie about this.
If you lie, you'll be in huge trouble.

414
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:47,110
- You hear me?
- I'm sorry.

415
00:29:47,810 --> 00:29:49,040
I'm really sorry.

416
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:51,250
I'll delete everything, I swear.

417
00:29:51,310 --> 00:29:52,680
- I'm really...
- Tell me the truth!

418
00:29:52,750 --> 00:29:53,750
Yes... I opened it.

419
00:29:54,120 --> 00:29:56,620
(Court)

420
00:30:04,830 --> 00:30:05,830
You're here early.

421
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:15,440
We keep running into each other.

422
00:30:16,340 --> 00:30:18,270
I thought we were on opposite sides.

423
00:30:22,210 --> 00:30:24,480
How's Chief Oh doing?

424
00:30:25,250 --> 00:30:26,250
You mean Chief Oh?

425
00:30:26,780 --> 00:30:28,250
Back when I was on the bench,

426
00:30:28,850 --> 00:30:30,920
everyone was in an uproar
about some hothead who had just joined,

427
00:30:32,390 --> 00:30:34,290
and he told me he was the one
who took you under his wing.

428
00:30:34,890 --> 00:30:38,430
You mean the troublemaker,
the top student at the Training Institute?

429
00:30:39,290 --> 00:30:40,800
You should worry less
about other people...

430
00:30:41,230 --> 00:30:42,900
and more about the murderer
you're defending.

431
00:30:46,330 --> 00:30:47,340
Hello.

432
00:30:51,870 --> 00:30:52,970
I know you're all very busy,

433
00:30:53,570 --> 00:30:55,110
so I appreciate your cooperation.

434
00:30:56,810 --> 00:30:59,210
The defense witness will be present,

435
00:30:59,950 --> 00:31:01,620
- correct?
- Yes.

436
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:03,720
That is correct.

437
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:09,260
At the next hearing,
based on the witnesses' testimonies,

438
00:31:09,490 --> 00:31:12,190
we'll determine if the crime's motive
was truly to heal people or not.

439
00:31:12,560 --> 00:31:14,160
We will examine that closely.

440
00:31:14,360 --> 00:31:15,730
A change in motive...

441
00:31:16,260 --> 00:31:19,530
- won't change the outcome of this case.
- But the sentencing guidelines...

442
00:31:20,540 --> 00:31:21,540
could change, though.

443
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:23,940
Look,

444
00:31:25,310 --> 00:31:27,410
he killed 17 people.

445
00:31:28,710 --> 00:31:29,940
Let's not do this here.

446
00:31:30,780 --> 00:31:31,980
Save it for the courtroom.

447
00:31:38,390 --> 00:31:40,150
You saw Reporter Jo's article, didn't you?

448
00:31:40,890 --> 00:31:42,320
Seemed pretty accurate to me.

449
00:31:43,320 --> 00:31:45,360
And what part of it is supposedly factual?

450
00:31:46,330 --> 00:31:47,330
Why?

451
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:51,230
If it's not true, then prove it.

452
00:31:51,900 --> 00:31:53,870
Stop whining about it like a child.

453
00:31:54,770 --> 00:31:55,770
A child?

454
00:31:58,110 --> 00:32:02,680
You were my student once.
So you still seem like one to me.

455
00:32:05,550 --> 00:32:06,680
(Reporter Jo Woo Cheol, Daehan Daily)

456
00:32:06,910 --> 00:32:08,850
Give my regards to Reporter Jo.

457
00:32:09,520 --> 00:32:10,520
I'll be on my way.

458
00:32:10,590 --> 00:32:12,590
(Criminal Court, Civil Petitions Office)

459
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:15,960
Hey, Reporter Jo, it's me.

460
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:18,690
- Attorney Park, we have a huge problem.
- What?

461
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:21,700
They're raiding the office right now!
It's total chaos!

462
00:32:26,670 --> 00:32:29,040
I'm almost there. I can see the office.
Hang on.

463
00:32:29,170 --> 00:32:33,780
No, they say my article is defamation,
violates the Comms Network Act,

464
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:37,010
and is an obstruction of justice.
Can they really raid an office for this?

465
00:32:40,180 --> 00:32:44,620
We know you're in there!
Open up before we break the door down!

466
00:32:51,360 --> 00:32:53,390
They're breaking the door. They broke it!
They're in!

467
00:32:53,390 --> 00:32:55,360
Please hurry... Hey, wait a minute!
Hold on!

468
00:32:55,460 --> 00:32:58,030
Hey, what do you think you're doing?
You don't even have a warrant!

469
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,200
Please cooperate.

470
00:33:00,500 --> 00:33:02,540
Let's just get this over with
quickly and painlessly.

471
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:05,610
Look who it is.
You should've just opened the door.

472
00:33:05,940 --> 00:33:09,510
- I was on the phone.
- Hey! Hold on a minute!

473
00:33:10,310 --> 00:33:11,310
Hold on, everyone.

474
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,520
Let me see the search warrant.

475
00:33:19,590 --> 00:33:21,190
This is all by the book.

476
00:33:22,090 --> 00:33:23,720
If we go back to Prosecutor Cha
empty-handed...

477
00:33:24,760 --> 00:33:25,890
So just step aside, please.

478
00:33:31,530 --> 00:33:32,530
Go ahead.

479
00:33:34,970 --> 00:33:37,140
What are you doing here anyway?

480
00:33:39,740 --> 00:33:40,980
But hold on a second!

481
00:33:43,340 --> 00:33:44,510
Everyone, just stop for a second.

482
00:33:45,950 --> 00:33:46,950
I...

483
00:33:48,050 --> 00:33:51,050
happen to share this office space.

484
00:33:52,090 --> 00:33:53,350
So anything that belongs to me...

485
00:33:54,490 --> 00:33:57,020
is absolutely off-limits. Understood?

486
00:34:01,060 --> 00:34:03,930
Sir, isn't this your desk?

487
00:34:05,370 --> 00:34:07,300
Your business cards are right here.

488
00:34:07,670 --> 00:34:08,670
About that...

489
00:34:11,370 --> 00:34:12,370
I put them in the wrong spot.

490
00:34:14,940 --> 00:34:17,140
This is my desk right here.

491
00:34:18,510 --> 00:34:21,320
Yes. That's right.
That's actually my desk.

492
00:34:21,420 --> 00:34:22,620
Yes, go ahead and take it.

493
00:34:23,420 --> 00:34:27,490
Sir, you're making this difficult.
This is clear obstruction of justice.

494
00:34:27,720 --> 00:34:30,990
Fine, then. Take whatever you want.

495
00:34:31,330 --> 00:34:34,400
But just know I'll be suing you
for larceny...

496
00:34:34,460 --> 00:34:38,970
for illegally taking my property.
We'll see who has the bigger headache.

497
00:34:39,830 --> 00:34:40,840
Just you wait.

498
00:34:45,940 --> 00:34:48,980
Man, what a chaotic day.
I thought I was going to lose my mind.

499
00:34:50,210 --> 00:34:51,480
That was Prosecutor Cha's doing, right?

500
00:34:52,180 --> 00:34:54,220
I heard she comes from
a pretty powerful family.

501
00:34:54,820 --> 00:34:56,320
She's the youngest daughter
of Sejin Group, right?

502
00:34:56,650 --> 00:34:57,650
That's right.

503
00:34:58,220 --> 00:35:00,790
So what's the bad blood between you two?

504
00:35:01,490 --> 00:35:03,360
She was my student back when
I taught at the Training Institute.

505
00:35:04,930 --> 00:35:06,560
But regardless of her family,

506
00:35:07,130 --> 00:35:09,730
she was the sharpest student
I ever taught...

507
00:35:11,370 --> 00:35:12,730
and the biggest pain in my neck.

508
00:35:12,970 --> 00:35:15,640
Gosh. For a student to be that rude
to her teacher...

509
00:35:17,740 --> 00:35:21,340
Man, today's been a mess.
When I'm stressed, I like to eat.

510
00:35:22,010 --> 00:35:25,380
Let's get a drink.
Hey, Min Gyeong! Over here!

511
00:35:26,310 --> 00:35:27,320
Attorney Park.

512
00:35:29,350 --> 00:35:30,950
- What's this?
- I invited her.

513
00:35:33,520 --> 00:35:34,720
Have you been well?

514
00:35:35,320 --> 00:35:36,820
Yes, I've been fine.

515
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:38,830
- It's been a while.
- Yes.

516
00:35:43,130 --> 00:35:45,430
So, are you really not going
to hire me back?

517
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:50,000
CEO Heo said Hae Gang will pay my salary,

518
00:35:50,100 --> 00:35:52,670
and that it's okay for me
to come and help you.

519
00:35:52,870 --> 00:35:55,280
Just stay at Hae Gang
and keep doing your job there.

520
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:57,080
Attorney Park.

521
00:35:58,710 --> 00:36:02,150
After you left, I wasn't assigned
to a new supervising attorney,

522
00:36:02,220 --> 00:36:04,950
so all I do every day is make copies.
This has to be better than that.

523
00:36:05,490 --> 00:36:06,890
Gosh, what are you talking about?

524
00:36:11,260 --> 00:36:15,130
Attorney Park.
What if we let Min Gyeong here...

525
00:36:15,530 --> 00:36:17,160
try to meet with a witness?

526
00:36:17,530 --> 00:36:18,530
The witnesses?

527
00:36:19,300 --> 00:36:21,200
You haven't secured a witness yet?

528
00:36:21,940 --> 00:36:23,470
Not yet.

529
00:36:23,740 --> 00:36:27,580
Since it's a serial murder case,
most witnesses are reluctant to cooperate.

530
00:36:30,910 --> 00:36:32,480
Then let me give it a try.

531
00:36:32,980 --> 00:36:33,980
What?

532
00:36:34,450 --> 00:36:37,250
I happen to be amazing
at getting people on board.

533
00:36:38,250 --> 00:36:39,720
For example, at my college festival,

534
00:36:39,950 --> 00:36:43,720
I set up all the lonely students
on group dates,

535
00:36:43,990 --> 00:36:47,460
and our pop-up bar broke the all-time
school sales record. That was all me.

536
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:51,400
But...

537
00:36:51,830 --> 00:36:55,670
- Recruiting a witness isn't exactly...
- You don't need a certificate for that.

538
00:36:56,300 --> 00:36:59,370
I don't have a certificate,
but I do have confidence.

539
00:37:00,170 --> 00:37:04,610
Maybe it's because
we're a couple of dreary faces...

540
00:37:04,850 --> 00:37:06,610
that it hasn't been working out.

541
00:37:07,210 --> 00:37:08,750
I know I can do a really good job.

542
00:37:09,380 --> 00:37:10,380
Please?

543
00:37:13,150 --> 00:37:15,790
For crying out loud.
What's gotten into you two?

544
00:37:17,260 --> 00:37:18,590
All right, fine. Then...

545
00:37:19,030 --> 00:37:23,560
Min Gyeong has no field experience,
so Reporter Jo, show her the ropes.

546
00:37:23,760 --> 00:37:25,970
Of course. That's my specialty.

547
00:37:27,130 --> 00:37:29,800
Min Gyeong, looking forward to working
with you. I'm Jo Woo Cheol.

548
00:37:29,870 --> 00:37:31,310
Hey, I'm just going to speak casually.

549
00:37:31,940 --> 00:37:33,670
Since you decided
to speak informally first,

550
00:37:34,610 --> 00:37:35,740
I'll do the same.

551
00:37:36,640 --> 00:37:39,310
- What?
- I'm just kidding, sir.

552
00:37:40,180 --> 00:37:43,180
- Well, then, shall we have a drink?
- All right.

553
00:37:43,450 --> 00:37:45,320
- All right, glasses up.
- Yes.

554
00:37:45,390 --> 00:37:47,460
- Cheers.
- Good.

555
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:52,830
Lee Woo Gyeom will surely pay
for his crimes, right?

556
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:56,430
But if it's true that he really cured
an incurable disease...

557
00:37:57,160 --> 00:37:59,170
so that he can help even more people,

558
00:37:59,470 --> 00:38:01,000
we have to at least give it a shot,
don't we?

559
00:38:06,140 --> 00:38:07,140
Ma'am.

560
00:38:07,940 --> 00:38:12,780
For the other patients and families
who are going through the same pain,

561
00:38:13,310 --> 00:38:14,320
please,

562
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:16,820
I'm begging you.

563
00:38:19,690 --> 00:38:20,690
I understand.

564
00:38:22,460 --> 00:38:23,460
I'll testify.

565
00:38:26,130 --> 00:38:27,330
Thank you, ma'am.

566
00:38:29,300 --> 00:38:30,300
There's something.

567
00:38:33,270 --> 00:38:34,440
I received this.

568
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:36,070
(From Lee Woo Gyeom)

569
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:48,220
(To the sea)

570
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:52,420
What in the world is this letter?
Did Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom really write this?

571
00:38:55,220 --> 00:38:58,590
If word gets out that I was sick,
it'll hurt my reputation at work.

572
00:38:59,660 --> 00:39:01,100
Please don't worry.

573
00:39:01,430 --> 00:39:03,960
Information about witnesses
is kept strictly confidential.

574
00:39:04,270 --> 00:39:05,900
- And we'll...
- But this is going too far.

575
00:39:06,430 --> 00:39:08,770
You're threatening to leak
my personal information to the press?

576
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:20,010
You can promise me that nothing
will happen to my Sang Woo, right?

577
00:39:20,550 --> 00:39:21,980
Look, I'll agree to testify,

578
00:39:23,050 --> 00:39:24,220
but I won't be threatened like this.

579
00:39:24,850 --> 00:39:27,290
I promise I'll do whatever it takes...

580
00:39:27,860 --> 00:39:31,090
to make sure you're not harmed by this.
I'm counting on you.

581
00:39:33,730 --> 00:39:36,260
This is the only way
the witnesses will testify.

582
00:39:36,330 --> 00:39:38,570
Nothing good will come
from provoking the witnesses.

583
00:39:38,670 --> 00:39:40,430
You have to provoke them
to get a reaction.

584
00:39:40,630 --> 00:39:44,370
You think all witnesses are on your side?
They could do something unpredictable.

585
00:39:47,610 --> 00:39:48,610
From now on,

586
00:39:49,110 --> 00:39:51,850
everything and anything
related to this trial,

587
00:39:52,610 --> 00:39:53,810
you run by me first.

588
00:39:54,750 --> 00:39:55,750
Got it?

589
00:40:06,460 --> 00:40:07,460
Yes.

590
00:40:13,130 --> 00:40:14,130
Prosecutor Cha.

591
00:40:14,700 --> 00:40:16,040
Here's the defense's witness list.

592
00:40:16,300 --> 00:40:17,300
Thank you.

593
00:40:17,770 --> 00:40:19,310
The mother of a patient
Lee Woo Gyeom saved...

594
00:40:19,370 --> 00:40:21,840
and an actual patient he treated
are being called as witnesses.

595
00:40:23,680 --> 00:40:25,110
Polio.

596
00:40:26,250 --> 00:40:27,250
Blood cancer.

597
00:40:30,420 --> 00:40:32,220
(Kang Sang Woo, 18 years old,
Congenital incurable polio)

598
00:40:32,290 --> 00:40:33,290
Kang Sang Woo.

599
00:40:33,890 --> 00:40:35,190
Incurable polio.

600
00:40:37,020 --> 00:40:39,890
He had never walked a single step
in his life.

601
00:40:40,690 --> 00:40:41,700
Right.

602
00:40:42,130 --> 00:40:46,130
Apparently, at a support group
for families with incurable diseases,

603
00:40:46,970 --> 00:40:50,900
Sang Woo's mother met Lee Woo Gyeom
by Song Tae Jin's sister.

604
00:40:52,540 --> 00:40:57,380
Mr. Song had terminal blood cancer,
but he's now been declared fully cured.

605
00:40:57,910 --> 00:40:59,450
Of the six patients...

606
00:40:59,450 --> 00:41:00,580
with incurable diseases
that Lee Woo Gyeom treated,

607
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:02,950
we've been unable to contact
the other four.

608
00:41:03,080 --> 00:41:05,750
Let's focus on the confirmed witnesses,
Kang Sang Woo's mother...

609
00:41:06,050 --> 00:41:07,660
and Mr. Song Tae Jin.

610
00:41:08,590 --> 00:41:11,230
The court will absolutely want to know...

611
00:41:11,230 --> 00:41:14,860
how Lee Woo Gyeom treated these people.

612
00:41:14,860 --> 00:41:17,030
So the question is how, in what way,

613
00:41:17,600 --> 00:41:19,330
we should disclose that. That's...

614
00:41:20,870 --> 00:41:22,170
That's the challenge.

615
00:41:26,210 --> 00:41:27,210
Attorney Park.

616
00:41:29,410 --> 00:41:32,580
You're worried about that letter he sent
to the witnesses, aren't you?

617
00:41:33,310 --> 00:41:34,320
Yes.

618
00:41:34,880 --> 00:41:35,880
The witnesses...

619
00:41:36,550 --> 00:41:38,290
I didn't want to force them to testify.

620
00:41:39,390 --> 00:41:42,260
Should we file for a postponement then?

621
00:41:42,720 --> 00:41:43,720
No, no.

622
00:41:44,360 --> 00:41:48,960
Given how impulsive Lee Woo Gyeom is,
there's no telling what he might do next.

623
00:41:50,300 --> 00:41:52,530
Let's find a better option for now.

624
00:41:53,400 --> 00:41:54,800
And do our absolute best...

625
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:56,800
to be prepared.

626
00:41:56,870 --> 00:42:01,140
Well then, no time like the present.
Let's get right to it, good?

627
00:42:01,410 --> 00:42:02,410
Sure, sounds good.

628
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:05,510
I'd much rather pull an all-nighter
than just be on copy duty.

629
00:42:05,680 --> 00:42:08,880
So, should I finally show you
what I'm made of?

630
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:30,870
- Thanks for all your hard work.
- Good job.

631
00:42:31,240 --> 00:42:32,240
- Bye.
- See you later.

632
00:42:45,790 --> 00:42:49,060
Today is the 4th hearing of the 1st trial
of the Lee Woo Gyeom case.

633
00:42:49,260 --> 00:42:52,260
The focus of this trial
is expected to be...

634
00:42:52,260 --> 00:42:55,060
on the witnesses' testimony
about the treatment.

635
00:42:55,660 --> 00:42:56,900
Witness.

636
00:42:56,900 --> 00:43:01,140
Is it true you entrusted the defendant,
Lee Woo Gyeom,

637
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:03,040
with treating your son, Sang Woo,

638
00:43:03,870 --> 00:43:07,070
- for his polio?
- Yes.

639
00:43:07,910 --> 00:43:08,980
That's correct.

640
00:43:09,540 --> 00:43:12,450
Then could you please describe
what happened at that time?

641
00:43:13,080 --> 00:43:15,420
He came with a bag of medical instruments.

642
00:43:16,080 --> 00:43:17,080
And...

643
00:43:18,120 --> 00:43:20,790
he injected what he called a "cure"
into Sang Woo's arm.

644
00:43:21,020 --> 00:43:24,760
And what were Sang Woo's symptoms
after the injection?

645
00:43:25,130 --> 00:43:27,190
Sang Woo seemed tired and fell asleep.

646
00:43:28,260 --> 00:43:29,730
He didn't wake up until dawn.

647
00:43:30,430 --> 00:43:31,430
How do you...

648
00:43:32,100 --> 00:43:34,970
- remember that after all this time?
- That morning,

649
00:43:36,970 --> 00:43:39,370
Sang Woo suddenly cried out and stood up.

650
00:43:41,910 --> 00:43:42,910
He stood up?

651
00:43:45,050 --> 00:43:46,550
So that everyone
in this court can hear you,

652
00:43:48,250 --> 00:43:49,950
please say that again...

653
00:43:50,880 --> 00:43:51,990
in a loud, clear voice.

654
00:43:53,320 --> 00:43:54,320
Yes.

655
00:43:55,260 --> 00:43:56,420
He stood up!

656
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:04,030
Could you describe that moment...

657
00:44:05,670 --> 00:44:07,370
in more detail?

658
00:44:08,600 --> 00:44:11,270
"Mom! Mom, look at this!"

659
00:44:12,510 --> 00:44:14,210
That's what he shouted.

660
00:44:15,040 --> 00:44:18,710
I was shocked and rushed to his room,
and when I got there,

661
00:44:20,410 --> 00:44:22,620
he was standing on his own two feet.

662
00:44:25,450 --> 00:44:26,620
That's right.

663
00:44:26,920 --> 00:44:29,890
Not once in 18 years.

664
00:44:30,390 --> 00:44:32,290
Sang Woo, who could never stand,

665
00:44:32,290 --> 00:44:35,360
was standing there,
completely on his own,

666
00:44:35,860 --> 00:44:38,630
right there in front of the witness.

667
00:44:39,670 --> 00:44:40,930
Witness,

668
00:44:41,540 --> 00:44:42,900
that is the truth, is it not?

669
00:44:43,540 --> 00:44:44,540
Yes.

670
00:44:45,140 --> 00:44:48,010
- He was standing all on his own.
- And after that,

671
00:44:48,780 --> 00:44:52,380
did Sang Woo's condition get worse,
or did it not?

672
00:44:52,610 --> 00:44:53,810
It did not.

673
00:44:54,310 --> 00:44:56,450
It was as if Sang Woo
had been given a new life.

674
00:44:57,120 --> 00:44:59,190
He told me how incredibly grateful he was
to Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom.

675
00:45:01,490 --> 00:45:03,020
He asked me to be sure to tell him that.

676
00:45:11,230 --> 00:45:12,300
Thank you.

677
00:45:14,230 --> 00:45:15,640
I have no further questions, Your Honor.

678
00:45:20,970 --> 00:45:23,480
Prosecutor.
You may begin your cross-examination.

679
00:45:25,480 --> 00:45:30,120
Witness, how many hospitals gave you
the incurable polio diagnosis for him?

680
00:45:31,180 --> 00:45:32,950
Around seven, I believe.

681
00:45:33,120 --> 00:45:36,520
And did you tell each new hospital
of the previous diagnosis?

682
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:41,060
Yes. So they'd know
what treatments he'd already had.

683
00:45:41,130 --> 00:45:42,600
Was that really the reason?

684
00:45:44,500 --> 00:45:48,770
Your insurance payouts for Sang Woo
were over 80,000 dollars in total.

685
00:45:49,000 --> 00:45:51,770
Isn't it true
you couldn't risk a different diagnosis?

686
00:45:51,870 --> 00:45:52,870
Your Honor.

687
00:45:53,470 --> 00:45:57,210
This line of questioning
is completely irrelevant...

688
00:45:57,280 --> 00:45:58,710
to the efficacy of the treatment.

689
00:46:01,950 --> 00:46:04,280
I am trying to establish that
if she intentionally shared the diagnosis,

690
00:46:04,350 --> 00:46:07,120
even if the incurable polio
was a misdiagnosis,

691
00:46:07,190 --> 00:46:10,520
the same diagnosis
would simply have been repeated.

692
00:46:11,830 --> 00:46:14,060
I'll allow it. You may continue.

693
00:46:22,400 --> 00:46:26,140
I'd like to call Seo Yeong Seok
from the National Forensic Service.

694
00:46:26,240 --> 00:46:30,440
When a prior diagnosis is shared,
the same mistake is more likely to occur.

695
00:46:30,740 --> 00:46:33,250
Can't they just ignore
the previous records?

696
00:46:33,510 --> 00:46:38,420
When you see dozens of patients a day,
it's hard to question the first diagnosis.

697
00:46:38,490 --> 00:46:40,720
What about in the case of Kang Sang Woo?

698
00:46:41,520 --> 00:46:44,190
Since there are no recorded cases
of a full recovery from incurable polio,

699
00:46:44,420 --> 00:46:48,430
- I think Sang Woo had another disease.
- Just a moment.

700
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:52,000
- So the diagnosis was a misdiagnosis?
- Yes.

701
00:46:53,070 --> 00:46:56,400
The disease most often misdiagnosed
as incurable polio...

702
00:46:57,240 --> 00:46:58,440
is Segawa's disease.

703
00:47:02,310 --> 00:47:06,010
The two present such similar symptoms
that even doctors get confused. However,

704
00:47:06,510 --> 00:47:09,080
unlike incurable polio,
Segawa's disease...

705
00:47:09,620 --> 00:47:10,850
is completely curable.

706
00:47:11,750 --> 00:47:16,490
In your expert opinion, what he treated
was not incurable polio, is that correct?

707
00:47:16,560 --> 00:47:17,720
Yes, that is correct.

708
00:47:17,820 --> 00:47:21,900
To come out now and say
Sang Woo had Segawa's disease...

709
00:47:22,500 --> 00:47:25,070
You can't possibly conclude that, can you?

710
00:47:26,030 --> 00:47:28,870
It's more of a stretch to believe
an incurable disease was cured.

711
00:47:29,640 --> 00:47:30,900
Either way,

712
00:47:31,670 --> 00:47:33,540
the defendant, Lee Yu Gyeom...

713
00:47:34,140 --> 00:47:37,610
- It's a fact that he did treat him.
- Your Honor,

714
00:47:37,840 --> 00:47:41,420
the defense submitted no prior evidence
regarding Segawa's disease.

715
00:47:41,520 --> 00:47:42,720
Sustained.

716
00:47:43,020 --> 00:47:46,520
Attorney Park. Confine your questions
to the defendant's original claim.

717
00:47:47,890 --> 00:47:48,890
Nothing further.

718
00:47:51,730 --> 00:47:53,460
The court will recess for 30 minutes.

719
00:47:53,930 --> 00:47:56,330
And then proceed with the examination
of the second witness.

720
00:47:59,100 --> 00:48:00,130
Let's go.

721
00:48:02,900 --> 00:48:04,540
(Defendant)

722
00:48:04,670 --> 00:48:06,870
- Attorney Park.
- Attorney Park.

723
00:48:08,210 --> 00:48:09,210
Did you get a hold of him?

724
00:48:09,610 --> 00:48:11,410
I can't get in touch with Song Tae Jin.

725
00:48:13,450 --> 00:48:14,820
Right, keep trying.

726
00:48:15,580 --> 00:48:16,580
Okay.

727
00:48:17,750 --> 00:48:18,750
Attorney Park,

728
00:48:19,020 --> 00:48:20,750
please begin your examination
of the second witness.

729
00:48:21,090 --> 00:48:22,160
Your Honor.

730
00:48:23,760 --> 00:48:25,430
There's an issue with
the witness's appearance,

731
00:48:26,130 --> 00:48:28,130
so I request a postponement.

732
00:48:31,130 --> 00:48:34,270
Isn't witness testimony
the crux of this trial?

733
00:48:35,270 --> 00:48:40,070
A postponement is unacceptable.
The witness is present in the courtroom.

734
00:48:43,240 --> 00:48:45,180
Attorney Park,
what is the meaning of this?

735
00:48:50,650 --> 00:48:51,790
Your Honor.

736
00:48:52,150 --> 00:48:56,260
If the defense is not going to call
Mr. Song Tae Jin to the stand,

737
00:48:56,490 --> 00:48:58,890
I request that the prosecution be allowed
to call him as our witness.

738
00:49:00,090 --> 00:49:02,860
Your Honor, the witness
the prosecution is referring to...

739
00:49:02,930 --> 00:49:04,830
has been watching
the previous witness's testimony...

740
00:49:04,900 --> 00:49:07,730
and is likely feeling a great deal
of psychological distress.

741
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:12,170
So, I object to the prosecution's request
to call him to the stand.

742
00:49:14,340 --> 00:49:15,710
Both of you, please be seated.

743
00:49:21,780 --> 00:49:24,990
The court will confer,
and then issue a ruling.

744
00:49:35,260 --> 00:49:37,860
The prosecution's request
to call the witness...

745
00:49:38,670 --> 00:49:39,800
is granted.

746
00:49:49,780 --> 00:49:50,780
Witness.

747
00:49:57,380 --> 00:50:01,450
Is it true you also received treatment
from the defendant, Mr. Lee Yu Gyeom?

748
00:50:04,290 --> 00:50:05,760
Yes, that's correct.

749
00:50:06,560 --> 00:50:07,990
And were you completely cured?

750
00:50:12,470 --> 00:50:16,600
No, I wasn't cured.
I'm receiving medical treatment again.

751
00:50:17,470 --> 00:50:21,110
That man is not a doctor.
He's a complete con man.

752
00:50:21,370 --> 00:50:25,380
He threatened to leak private information,
my medical records, and family details.

753
00:50:26,150 --> 00:50:27,180
Don't be fooled by him.

754
00:50:29,650 --> 00:50:30,750
Nothing further, Your Honor.

755
00:50:41,600 --> 00:50:43,530
(High Court, District Court)

756
00:50:45,730 --> 00:50:46,730
Excuse me, Song Tae Jin.

757
00:50:47,770 --> 00:50:48,770
Wait a second.

758
00:50:52,840 --> 00:50:53,840
What on earth...

759
00:50:54,740 --> 00:50:57,310
- Why did you do that?
- Do what?

760
00:50:58,040 --> 00:51:00,510
I'm asking why you testified
like that in court.

761
00:51:00,980 --> 00:51:05,350
Because it's the truth.
I'm getting worse again.

762
00:51:06,120 --> 00:51:07,320
But you clearly said...

763
00:51:07,590 --> 00:51:10,860
- You were cured.
- I thought I was.

764
00:51:11,660 --> 00:51:13,060
But it came back.

765
00:51:16,330 --> 00:51:17,730
Don't you ever...

766
00:51:18,300 --> 00:51:19,800
come near me again.

767
00:51:31,240 --> 00:51:32,480
Attorney Park.

768
00:51:33,950 --> 00:51:35,580
Is this really the best you can do?

769
00:51:36,450 --> 00:51:38,320
How are we supposed to
win the trial like this?

770
00:51:38,790 --> 00:51:40,320
You're the one who caused this mess.

771
00:51:40,750 --> 00:51:42,220
You're blaming me for this?

772
00:51:42,290 --> 00:51:45,230
Yes. This whole thing happened because
you threatened Song Tae Jin.

773
00:51:45,290 --> 00:51:47,730
I think you're mistaken.

774
00:51:48,760 --> 00:51:50,330
If I can't prove my abilities,

775
00:51:51,430 --> 00:51:52,600
Min Seo will die too.

776
00:51:55,740 --> 00:51:58,770
You... I told you...

777
00:51:59,570 --> 00:52:01,340
not to talk so casually about my daughter.

778
00:52:01,410 --> 00:52:05,050
That's my point.
Just let me prove myself already.

779
00:52:05,150 --> 00:52:08,550
That's all it would take,
but you were fumbling with the witnesses,

780
00:52:08,620 --> 00:52:10,150
so I had to step in.

781
00:52:10,220 --> 00:52:13,090
You stepped in and ruined everything,
you son of a bitch!

782
00:52:15,220 --> 00:52:17,790
(Fresh Sashimi)

783
00:52:17,790 --> 00:52:18,860
Mr. Song Tae Jin.

784
00:52:21,800 --> 00:52:23,400
I'm sorry for showing up unannounced.

785
00:52:24,130 --> 00:52:27,000
If you don't mind,
I'd just like to ask you a few things.

786
00:52:29,840 --> 00:52:33,570
They told me I was completely cured,
but since he's not a real doctor,

787
00:52:34,240 --> 00:52:36,010
so I got worried and went back
to the hospital.

788
00:52:37,440 --> 00:52:40,250
Sure enough, I had a relapse.

789
00:52:41,180 --> 00:52:45,890
So in other words,
Lee Woo Gyeom's treatment didn't work?

790
00:52:46,390 --> 00:52:47,420
That's right.

791
00:52:48,990 --> 00:52:51,520
In time, Sang Woo...

792
00:52:52,360 --> 00:52:53,830
will end up just like me.

793
00:52:54,660 --> 00:52:58,030
But after his treatment
from Lee Woo Gyeom,

794
00:52:58,100 --> 00:52:59,730
Sang Woo never received
any hospital treatments.

795
00:53:02,300 --> 00:53:06,040
To be clear, you went to the hospital
after Lee Woo Gyeom's supposed cure?

796
00:53:06,170 --> 00:53:07,170
Yes.

797
00:53:08,710 --> 00:53:09,710
So then...

798
00:53:10,710 --> 00:53:13,880
Prosecutor, you can't let the patient
get another procedure.

799
00:53:14,310 --> 00:53:16,580
If it interferes with my methods,

800
00:53:17,480 --> 00:53:18,990
he'll never be able to recover.

801
00:53:24,390 --> 00:53:28,460
So your condition got worse
when you resumed hospital treatment.

802
00:53:29,200 --> 00:53:30,200
What?

803
00:53:31,600 --> 00:53:33,170
Not because of Lee Woo Gyeom.

804
00:53:35,240 --> 00:53:37,740
Your records and witnesses
have been refuted,

805
00:53:39,040 --> 00:53:42,440
- so how can I possibly trust you anymore?
- What I want right now...

806
00:53:43,210 --> 00:53:46,550
is to prove my abilities
so I can treat people who are suffering.

807
00:53:46,810 --> 00:53:49,720
My intentions are good.
Why can't you convey that properly?

808
00:53:52,790 --> 00:53:53,790
Because...

809
00:53:54,850 --> 00:53:56,220
that's not what you really want.

810
00:53:56,760 --> 00:53:58,730
Would someone
with such good intentions...

811
00:53:59,530 --> 00:54:01,190
treat the witnesses like garbage?

812
00:54:03,730 --> 00:54:05,300
You, be honest with me.

813
00:54:06,670 --> 00:54:09,100
Why do you really want to prove yourself?

814
00:54:10,940 --> 00:54:12,070
You want me to tell you?

815
00:54:14,470 --> 00:54:15,940
Are you sure you can handle it?

816
00:54:22,950 --> 00:54:24,920
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
